# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers:
The structure consists of 8 building blocks arranged in 3 distinct layers:
- Bottom layer: Two orange cylindrical columns
- Middle layer: A yellow rectangular beam supporting a red house-like structure with yellow semi-circular arches
- Top layer: A tall orange cylindrical column topped with an orange triangular roof

## Spatial Relationships:
- Two orange cylindrical columns stand vertically as the foundation
- A horizontal yellow rectangular beam connects these two columns
- A red house-like structure with arched openings sits on top of the yellow beam
- Two yellow semi-circular arches are placed inside the red house structure
- A taller orange cylindrical column rises from behind the red house
- An orange triangular roof piece sits at the top of the tall column

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Looking at the block dictionary, I need the following blocks:
- Block #8: Vertical orange cylinder (used 3 times for all columns)
- Block #4: Horizontal yellow rectangular beam
- Block #1: Red house structure with arched opening
- Block #10: Yellow semi-circular arch (used 2 times)
- Block #15: Orange triangular roof piece

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 8
    Step2: Move block with index 8
    Step3: Move block with index 4
    Step4: Move block with index 1
    Step5: Move block with index 10
    Step6: Move block with index 10
    Step7: Move block with index 8
    Step8: Move block with index 15
}
```

This assembly sequence builds the structure from bottom to top, starting with the foundation columns, adding the connecting beam, then the house structure with arches, and finally completing with the tall column and roof.
